<paragraph blockId="1.[264,780,1412,1438]" box="[264,780,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<heading bold="true" box="[264,780,1412,1438]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,780,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Lom &amp; Nigrelli, 1970" authorityName="Lom &amp; Nigrelli" authorityYear="1970" box="[351,780,1412,1438]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Brooklynella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[351,507,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Brooklynella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lom" box="[515,780,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" refString="Lom, J. &amp; Nigrelli, R. F. (1970) Brooklynella hostilis n. g., n. sp., a pathogenic cyrtophorine ciliate in marine fishes. Journal of Protozoology, 17, 224 - 232." type="journal article" year="1970">
Lom &amp; Nigrelli, 
<number box="[721,780,1412,1438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1487,1753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Although the 
<typeStatus box="[430,481,1487,1513]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName box="[584,829,1487,1512]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Brooklynella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="hostilis">
<emphasis box="[584,829,1487,1512]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Brooklynella hostilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been characterized in detail (
<bibRefCitation author="Lom" pageId="1" pageNumber="49" refString="Lom, J. &amp; Nigrelli, R. F. (1970) Brooklynella hostilis n. g., n. sp., a pathogenic cyrtophorine ciliate in marine fishes. Journal of Protozoology, 17, 224 - 232." type="journal article" year="1970">
Lom &amp; Nigrelli 
<number box="[362,424,1527,1553]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the genus, in our opinion, has not been clearly circumscribed. Based on the data available, an improved definition of the genus is here supplied.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1487,1753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,787,1606,1632]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Improved diagnosis for 
<taxonomicName box="[620,776,1606,1632]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Brooklynella" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[620,776,1606,1632]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Brooklynella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[797,986,1607,1633]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="family">Hartmannulidae</taxonomicName>
with a definitive podite, of which the base is located at posterior ventral portion of cell, but not surrounded by somatic kineties; postoral and left kineties considerably shorter than right kineties, terminate at about the same level of post­equator rather than progressively posteriorly shortened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
